.TH "lpfc_sli_check_eratt" 9 "lpfc_sli_check_eratt" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
lpfc_sli_check_eratt \- check error attention events
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" lpfc_sli_check_eratt
.BI "(struct lpfc_hba *phba "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "phba" 12
Pointer to HBA context.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function is called from timer soft interrupt context to check HBA's
error attention register bit for error attention events.

This function returns 1 when there is Error Attention in the Host Attention
Register and returns 0 otherwise.
